## Alphabetic list of titles

### A

*   [Abhandlungen aus dem Mathematischen Seminar der Universität Hamburg](/Abhandlungen_aus_dem_Mathematischen_Seminar_der_Universit%C3%A4t_Hamburg) – A rather Germanic title, suggesting rigor and a certain institutional weight. I imagine it’s where proofs go to be thoroughly dissected.
*   [Abstract and Applied Analysis](/Abstract_and_Applied_Analysis) – Exactly what it sounds like. Pure theory meeting practical application, a bridge that’s often more precarious than it appears.
*   [Acta Applicandae Mathematicae](/Acta_Applicandae_Mathematicae) – Latin for "Applied Mathematics Actions." More Latin, more application. It’s like they’re trying to convince us it’s important.
*   [Acta Arithmetica](/Acta_Arithmetica) – "Arithmetic Actions." Numbers, I suppose. The bedrock, or the quicksand, depending on your perspective.
*   [Acta Mathematica](/Acta_Mathematica) – The grand dame. If you’re publishing here, you’re probably not worried about rent.
*   [Acta Mathematica Hungarica](/Acta_Mathematica_Hungarica) – Hungarian contributions to the global mathematical discourse. A solid entry.
*   [Acta Mathematica Sinica](/Acta_Mathematica_Sinica) – From China. The East is a significant player in modern mathematics, a fact some still struggle to acknowledge.
*   [Acta Mathematicae Applicatae Sinica](/Acta_Mathematicae_Applicatae_Sinica) – More applied mathematics from China. Apparently, they’re quite busy.
*   [Acta Numerica](/Acta_Numerica) – Numbers again. This one is likely a survey or review of numerical methods. Useful, if you like that sort of thing.
*   [Acta Scientiarum Mathematicarum](/Acta_Scientiarum_Mathematicarum) – "Actions of Mathematical Sciences." Broad scope, sounds official.
*   [Advances in Applied Clifford Algebras](/Advances_in_Applied_Clifford_Algebras) – Clifford algebras. Niche, but apparently important enough to warrant dedicated "advances."
*   [Advances in Applied Mathematics](/Advances_in_Applied_Mathematics) – The applied side, seeking greater heights.
*   [Advances in Difference Equations](/Advances_in_Difference_Equations) – Equations that differ. Sounds like a quest for the unknown, or a very specific kind of headache.
*   [Advances in Geometry](/Advances_in_Geometry) – Where shapes and spaces are explored with renewed vigor.
*   [Advances in Mathematics](/Advances_in_Mathematics) – A general catch-all for cutting-edge mathematical research. Ambitious.
*   [Advances in Operator Theory](/Advances_in_Operator_Theory) – Operator theory. For those who find functions and operators insufficiently abstract.
*   [Advances in Theoretical and Mathematical Physics](/Advances_in_Theoretical_and_Mathematical_Physics) – Where the universe's underlying logic is debated with equations. Often more philosophy than physics, if you ask me.
*   [Algebra & Number Theory](/Algebra_%26_Number_Theory) – Two fundamental pillars of mathematics, brought together. A classic pairing.
*   [Algebra Colloquium](/Algebra_Colloquium) – A gathering of algebraic minds, presumably.
*   [Algebra i Logika](/Algebra_i_Logika) – "Algebra and Logic" in Russian. A historical powerhouse of logic and algebra.
*   [Algebra Universalis](/Algebra_Universalis) – "Universal Algebra." The title suggests a grand, sweeping ambition.
*   [Algebraic & Geometric Topology](/Algebraic_%26_Geometric_Topology) – The intersection of abstract structures and spatial intuition. A field that can make your head spin.
*   Algebraic Combinatorics – A burgeoning field, I'm told. Deals with the algebraic structure of combinatorial objects.
*   [American Journal of Mathematics](/American_Journal_of_Mathematics) – A venerable institution. Publishing here is a mark of serious achievement.
*   [American Mathematical Monthly](/American_Mathematical_Monthly) – More accessible than some, aimed at a broader mathematical audience. Good for keeping the troops informed.
*   [Analysis and Applications](/Analysis_and_Applications) – The persistent link between theoretical analysis and practical problems.
*   [The Analyst, or, Mathematical Museum](/The_Analyst,_or,_Mathematical_Museum) – Sounds quaint. Probably one of those historical journals where they still wrote like gentlemen.
*   [Annales Academiae Scientiarum Fennicae. Mathematica](/Annales_Academiae_Scientiarum_Fennicae._Mathematica) – Finnish contributions to mathematical science. Precision and perhaps a touch of melancholic beauty.
*   [Annales de Gergonne](/Annales_de_Gergonne) – A historical French journal. Named after a mathematician, likely.
*   [Annales de l'Institut Fourier](/Annales_de_l%27Institut_Fourier) – Based in Grenoble, France. Another solid European mathematical publication.
*   [Annales Henri Poincaré](/Annales_Henri_Poincar%C3%A9) – Honoring a titan. Likely focuses on mathematical physics and related areas.
*   [Annales Scientifiques de l'École Normale Supérieure](/Annales_Scientifiques_de_l%27%C3%89cole_Normale_Sup%C3%A9rieure) – Prestigious French journal from a renowned institution. Top-tier research.
*   [Annals of Applied Probability](/Annals_of_Applied_Probability) – Where probability theory meets the real world. Often involves modeling uncertainty.
*   [Annals of Combinatorics](/Annals_of_Combinatorics) – The study of discrete structures, counting, and arrangements. A field with surprising depth.
*   [Annals of Functional Analysis](/Annals_of_Functional_Analysis) – Functional analysis, a cornerstone of modern mathematics, particularly in physics and applied fields.
*   [Annals of Mathematical Statistics](/Annals_of_Mathematical_Statistics) – The historical predecessor to a more modern statistical journal. Statistics has a complicated relationship with pure mathematics.
*   [Annals of Mathematics](/Annals_of_Mathematics) – Arguably one of the most prestigious mathematics journals in existence. If you publish here, you've likely done something significant.
*   [Annals of Probability](/Annals_of_Probability) – The pure theory of probability. Less messy than its applied counterpart.
*   [Annals of Statistics](/Annals_of_Statistics) – A leading journal in statistical theory and methods.
*   [Applied Mathematics and Mechanics (English Edition)](/Applied_Mathematics_and_Mechanics_(English_Edition)) – Russian research translated. Mechanics is applied math's close cousin.
*   [Archiv der Mathematik](/Archiv_der_Mathematik) – "Archive of Mathematics." Sounds like a repository for foundational work.
*   [Archive for Mathematical Logic](/Archive_for_Mathematical_Logic) – The formal underpinnings of mathematics. Where certainty is sought, or perhaps lost.
*   [Archive for Rational Mechanics and Analysis](/Archive_for_Rational_Mechanics_and_Analysis) – A journal with a long and distinguished history, covering fundamental work in theoretical mechanics and analysis.
*   [Arkiv för Matematik](/Arkiv_f%C3%B6r_Matematik) – Swedish for "Archive of Mathematics." More archives.
*   [Arnold Mathematical Journal](/Arnold_Mathematical_Journal) – Named after Vladimir Arnold, a brilliant and often controversial mathematician. Expect challenging and insightful work.
*   [Ars Combinatoria](/Ars_Combinatoria_(journal)) – "The Art of Combinatorics." A fitting name for a field that can be both intricate and beautiful.
*   [Ars Mathematica Contemporanea](/Ars_Mathematica_Contemporanea) – "Contemporary Mathematical Art." Suggests a modern and perhaps artistic approach to mathematics.
*   [Asia-Pacific Journal of Operational Research](/Asia-Pacific_Journal_of_Operational_Research) – Operational research is applied mathematics focused on decision-making. This one has a regional focus.
*   [Asian Journal of Mathematics](/Asian_Journal_of_Mathematics) – Another significant journal from the East.
*   [AStA Advances in Statistical Analysis](/AStA_Advances_in_Statistical_Analysis) – Statistical analysis, with an emphasis on new developments.
*   [Astérisque](/Ast%C3%A9risque) – A publication series from the French Mathematical Society, often publishing monographs or conference proceedings. Known for in-depth treatments.
*   [Automation and Remote Control](/Automation_and_Remote_Control) – While not purely mathematical, control theory and related mathematical concepts are crucial here.

### B

*   [Banach Journal of Mathematical Analysis](/Banach_Journal_of_Mathematical_Analysis) – Named after Stefan Banach, a giant of functional analysis. Expect rigorous analysis.
*   [Biometrics](/Biometrics_(journal)) – Statistics applied to biological sciences. Where numbers meet life.
*   [Biometrika](/Biometrika) – Another key journal for statistical theory, with a strong connection to biological applications.
*   [Biostatistics](/Biostatistics_(journal)) – Focused specifically on statistical methods in biological and health research.
*   [Brazilian Journal of Probability and Statistics](/Brazilian_Journal_of_Probability_and_Statistics) – Contributions from South America in these vital fields.
*   [Bulletin de la Société Mathématique de France](/Bulletin_de_la_Soci%C3%A9t%C3%A9_Math%C3%A9matique_de_France) – The official bulletin of the French Mathematical Society.
*   [Bulletin of Mathematical Biology](/Bulletin_of_Mathematical_Biology) – Where mathematical models are applied to biological systems.
*   [Bulletin of Symbolic Logic](/Bulletin_of_Symbolic_Logic) – The primary publication for the Association for Symbolic Logic. Essential for logicians.
*   [Bulletin of the American Mathematical Society](/Bulletin_of_the_American_Mathematical_Society) – Contains articles on current mathematical research and events, often written for a broader mathematical audience.
*   [Bulletin of the Belgian Mathematical Society](/Bulletin_of_the_Belgian_Mathematical_Society) – Belgian contributions to the mathematical world.
*   [Bulletin of the London Mathematical Society](/Bulletin_of_the_London_Mathematical_Society) – The LMS equivalent of the AMS Bulletin.
*   [Bulletin of Mathematical Sciences](/Bulletin_of_Mathematical_Sciences) – A journal focusing on important mathematical developments.
*   [Cahiers de Topologie et Géométrie Différentielle Catégoriques](/Cahiers_de_Topologie_et_G%C3%A9om%C3%A9trie_Diff%C3%A9rentielle_Cat%C3%A9goriques) – A very specialized journal focusing on category theory, topology, and differential geometry. Not for the faint of heart.
*   [Canadian Journal of Mathematics](/Canadian_Journal_of_Mathematics) – A highly respected journal from Canada.
*   [Canadian Mathematical Bulletin](/Canadian_Mathematical_Bulletin) – Another solid Canadian mathematical journal.
*   [Central European Journal of Mathematics](/Central_European_Journal_of_Mathematics) – Contributions from a historically rich mathematical region.
*   [Chinese Annals of Mathematics, Series B](/Chinese_Annals_of_Mathematics,_Series_B) – A significant publication outlet for Chinese mathematicians.
*   [College Mathematics Journal](/College_Mathematics_Journal) – Focused on mathematics relevant to undergraduate education.
*   [Combinatorica](/Combinatorica) – A leading journal dedicated to combinatorics.
*   [Commentarii Mathematici Helvetici](/Commentarii_Mathematici_Helvetici) – "Swiss Mathematical Comments." A prestigious journal from Switzerland.
*   [Communications in Contemporary Mathematics](/Communications_in_Contemporary_Mathematics) – Modern mathematical research, likely broad in scope.
*   [Communications in Mathematical Physics](/Communications_in_Mathematical_Physics) – A crucial journal for the intersection of mathematics and theoretical physics.
*   [Communications on Pure and Applied Mathematics](/Communications_on_Pure_and_Applied_Mathematics) – Highly regarded for publishing significant results in applied mathematics.
*   [Compositio Mathematica](/Compositio_Mathematica) – A journal known for publishing important and often groundbreaking work across various fields of mathematics.
*   [Comptes Rendus Mathématique](/Comptes_Rendus_Math%C3%A9matique) – The mathematical section of the French Academy of Sciences' Comptes Rendus.
*   [Computing](/Computing_(journal)) – While broader, it certainly includes significant mathematical and algorithmic content.
*   [Constructive Approximation](/Constructive_Approximation) – Focuses on approximation theory, where functions are approximated by simpler ones.
*   [COSMOS](/COSMOS_(journal)) – Likely related to mathematical modeling in cosmology or complex systems.
*   [Crelle's Journal](/Crelle%27s_Journal) (Journal fuer die Reine und Angewandte Mathematik) – "Journal for Pure and Applied Mathematics." One of the oldest and most respected mathematics journals. A true classic.

### D

*   [Differential Equations](/Differential_Equations_(journal)) – Exactly as it sounds. The study of equations involving derivatives. Fundamental.
*   [Discrete Analysis](/Discrete_Analysis) – A newer journal focusing on discrete mathematics and analysis.
*   [Discrete and Computational Geometry](/Discrete_and_Computational_Geometry) – The geometry of discrete structures, often with algorithmic applications.
*   [Discrete Mathematics](/Discrete_Mathematics_(journal)) – A broad journal covering all aspects of discrete mathematics.
*   [Discrete Applied Mathematics](/Discrete_Applied_Mathematics) – Where discrete structures meet real-world problems.
*   [Duke Mathematical Journal](/Duke_Mathematical_Journal) – A highly prestigious journal from Duke University, publishing significant research across mathematics.

### E

